Paper: hep-th/0101058

Date: 2001-01-10

Title: Stringy Spacetime Uncertainty as an Alternative to Inflation

Authors: Je-An Gu, Pei-Ming Ho, Sanjaye Ramgoolam

Comments: 9 pages, acknowledgement added

In this paper we point out that the spacetime uncertainty relation proposedfor string theory has strong cosmological implications that can solve theflatness problem and the horizon problem without the need of inflation. We makeminimal assumptions about the very early universe.